## Problem
33 ESLint errors blocking CI. Critical rules-of-hooks violations.

## Files to Fix

### 1. TodayCard.jsx - Hooks called conditionally
```javascript
// WRONG - hook inside condition
if (someCondition) {
  const [state, setState] = useState();
}

// RIGHT - always call hooks at top level
const [state, setState] = useState();
if (someCondition) {
  // use state here
}
```

### 2. AdminHeader.jsx - useClerk called conditionally
Move useClerk() call to component top level, before any conditions.

### 3. UserRoleContext.jsx - useUser called conditionally
Same fix - move hook to top level.

### 4. sw.js - 'clients' is not defined
Add to eslint globals or use proper service worker API:
```javascript
/* eslint-env serviceworker */
// Or
/* global clients */
```

### 5. Unused variables
Remove or prefix with underscore if intentionally unused.

## Goal
0 lint errors, remove continue-on-error from CI workflow.

Reply when fixed.

